01:13.656 --> 01:15.783
KLAUS:
I figured out how to open it.

01:16.868 --> 01:18.410
Can you?

01:18.828 --> 01:20.454
[BONNIE SCREAMS]

01:20.747 --> 01:22.623
[PANTING]

01:22.832 --> 01:24.249
[BANGING]

01:28.671 --> 01:30.339
[PHONE BEEPING]

01:32.258 --> 01:35.928
Let me out! Please!

01:36.846 --> 01:39.014
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

01:39.933 --> 01:41.225
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

01:48.566 --> 01:49.650
[BANGING]

01:49.859 --> 01:51.276
[GRUNTS]

01:51.486 --> 01:52.778
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

01:55.657 --> 01:58.659
Hey! I'm in here!

01:58.868 --> 01:59.993
I'm in here!

02:00.245 --> 02:01.995
[SCREAMS]

02:02.205 --> 02:03.956
I'm in here!

02:08.127 --> 02:10.628
BONNIE: I've been having these dreams
for days now.

02:10.839 --> 02:13.132
The witches are trying
to send me a message.

02:13.341 --> 02:16.135
ELENA: I just can't believe
you guys have kept this from me.

02:16.344 --> 02:18.804
Stefan thought if you knew
where the coffins were...

02:19.013 --> 02:22.224
...Klaus could threaten people to get
the information out of you.

02:22.851 --> 02:25.227
- So these are the rest of his family?
- Yeah.

02:25.436 --> 02:26.728
Elijah and two others.

02:27.313 --> 02:30.524
This one is the one we can't open.

02:31.734 --> 02:33.735
We don't know who's in it
or what's in it.

02:33.945 --> 02:36.530
Only that I think my dream's telling me
it will help kill Klaus.

02:36.739 --> 02:38.448
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

02:39.534 --> 02:42.369
- What are you doing?
- I needed her to know about the coffin.

02:42.579 --> 02:45.038
And I needed you to keep her
out of it, Bonnie.

02:45.248 --> 02:46.540
What are you gonna do?

02:46.749 --> 02:48.917
Are you gonna kidnap me
so that I won't tell anyone?

02:49.961 --> 02:51.670
Don't tempt me, Elena.

02:51.880 --> 02:53.755
I think I know who can open the coffin.

02:54.007 --> 02:55.924
And I need Elena to help me find her.

02:57.010 --> 02:59.386
Find who?
What are you talking about?

03:01.014 --> 03:03.599
BONNIE:
I couldn't place her face at first.

03:06.519 --> 03:08.604
Then I realized...

03:10.523 --> 03:12.399
Oh, my God. Bonnie.

03:15.695 --> 03:17.279
Who is this?

03:18.573 --> 03:19.948
It's my mom.

03:27.123 --> 03:28.415
Los Alamitos?

03:29.959 --> 03:32.586
BONNIE: Hmm, too old.
- Honolulu?

03:32.795 --> 03:34.588
- Ugh. I wish.
- Heh.

03:35.131 --> 03:37.299
- How many of these are there?
- A lot.

03:37.508 --> 03:41.803
I asked the sheriff's office to pull up
every Abby Bennett in the country.

03:42.013 --> 03:45.432
I know we haven't been able to really...
That things have been weird...

03:45.642 --> 03:49.561
...because of Jeremy.
So thank you for helping me with this.

03:49.771 --> 03:51.980
I know you have a lot to deal with.

03:52.232 --> 03:54.942
There's nothing more important,
Bonnie.

03:55.151 --> 03:59.029
It's surreal. Having to track down
a woman who bailed on her own kid.

03:59.239 --> 04:01.198
You know you don't have to, right?

04:01.407 --> 04:04.034
Let Stefan obsess over
opening up the coffin.

04:04.244 --> 04:07.704
- It doesn't have to fall on you.
- The coffin's spelled shut.

04:07.914 --> 04:09.331
That makes it a witch problem.

04:09.582 --> 04:11.333
So it does fall on me.

04:11.542 --> 04:13.669
I was bound to see my mother
sooner or later.

04:13.920 --> 04:15.545
Sooner.

04:16.630 --> 04:19.132
Abby Bennett Wilson,
Monroe, North Carolina.

04:19.341 --> 04:22.970
Born in Mystic Falls Hospital, graduated
Mystic Falls High, blah, blah, blah.

04:26.474 --> 04:29.601
A little compulsion helps speed up
the research process.

04:32.063 --> 04:34.064
- This is her.
DAMON: Yep. Road trip.

04:34.274 --> 04:35.482
I call shotgun.

04:35.692 --> 04:37.067
Yeah, no.

04:37.277 --> 04:39.653
- Want me in the back with you?
- You're not coming.

04:39.862 --> 04:41.446
Why? I'm the one who found her.

04:41.656 --> 04:45.867
Okay, Damon, look, Bonnie hasn't
seen her mom in over 15 years.

04:46.077 --> 04:49.329
We don't need your snarky commentary
narrating the experience.

04:55.628 --> 04:57.045
What's going on with you two?

04:57.964 --> 04:59.339
We kissed, now it's weird.

05:00.466 --> 05:01.842
Have a great trip.

05:17.066 --> 05:18.567
What are you doing here?

05:19.360 --> 05:20.527
I came to apologize.

05:21.237 --> 05:24.865
Heh. Apologize? You bit me.

05:25.074 --> 05:28.702
I could have died.
I think we're way past apologies, Tyler.

05:28.911 --> 05:31.705
That's the problem.
Klaus told me to do it and I said no.

05:31.914 --> 05:34.166
And then, it just happened anyway.

05:34.375 --> 05:36.918
Like it was completely
out of my control.

05:38.212 --> 05:39.880
That's why I had your mom call him.

05:43.259 --> 05:45.385
- Daddy?
- Hi, Caroline.

05:45.595 --> 05:47.929
TYLER: I thought since
he could resist compulsion...

05:48.181 --> 05:51.141
...maybe he could teach me
to resist the sire bond.

05:51.684 --> 05:52.934
Can you help him?

05:54.395 --> 05:55.645
I'm gonna try.

05:56.939 --> 05:59.900
- Why?
- Because he made a mistake.

06:00.610 --> 06:02.152
And now he wants to make good.

06:03.946 --> 06:05.739
And I understand that.

06:12.705 --> 06:15.082
ALARIC: Do you want anything else?
A beer?

06:15.291 --> 06:18.085
Oh, I'd love one,
but I've got rounds in 15 minutes...

06:18.294 --> 06:20.295
...and a drunk doctor is a bad doctor.

06:20.546 --> 06:22.130
Depends on what kind of drunk you are.

06:22.340 --> 06:23.507
- Angry.
- Oh.

06:23.800 --> 06:26.134
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

06:27.136 --> 06:29.805
- Thanks for lunch.
- Yeah, sure.

06:30.014 --> 06:33.475
Ahem, so, uh, next time dinner?

06:33.684 --> 06:35.602
Yeah, that'd be great.

06:35.812 --> 06:39.815
- Cool. Well, take care.
- Bye. Thanks.

06:42.693 --> 06:45.070
- Who's that?
- My doctor.

06:45.279 --> 06:46.321
- She's a doctor?
- Mm-hm.

06:46.531 --> 06:48.240
Ooh. What's the damage?

06:49.200 --> 06:52.619
- No damage.
- Come on, Ric, it's a fact of life.

06:52.829 --> 06:55.455
A girl that hot, that smart? Damage.

06:55.665 --> 06:57.916
Well, you know,
I've been looking for red flags.

06:58.126 --> 07:00.794
Her, uh, ex called her a psycho case
the other day.

07:01.003 --> 07:03.713
- If it comes from her ex it doesn't count.
ALARIC: You're right.

07:03.923 --> 07:06.758
- That's yours.
- Wonder what my exes would call me?

07:06.968 --> 07:08.635
Nothing, they're all dead.

07:09.512 --> 07:13.723
Hmm. Well, her ex is the medical examiner,
so he's dead-adjacent.

07:13.933 --> 07:16.476
- She dated a medical examiner?
- Mm-hm.

07:17.770 --> 07:20.605
I don't think he's dead-adjacent,
I think he's just dead.

07:20.815 --> 07:22.149
What?

07:22.358 --> 07:24.985
Murdered.
Sheriff's trying to keep a lid on it...

07:25.194 --> 07:28.196
...because he was staked in the chest
like a vampire.

07:30.324 --> 07:32.325
Meredith didn't say anything
about that.

07:32.535 --> 07:34.786
Well, red flag number two.

07:34.996 --> 07:37.456
- Who do you think killed him?
- I don't know.

07:37.665 --> 07:41.501
If I was a cop, your sexy doctor lady
friend would definitely be a suspect.

07:43.212 --> 07:45.213
[THE BLACK KEYS' "LONELY BOY"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

07:59.312 --> 08:02.481
- What are you doing here, Klaus?
- Enjoying our stalemate.

08:03.399 --> 08:06.276
- What do you want?
- Question is, what do you want?

08:06.486 --> 08:08.278
My hybrids left town
as you demanded...

08:08.488 --> 08:11.865
...so please tell me what I need to do
to get my family back.

08:12.074 --> 08:17.287
Well, ahem, see, Klaus, um...

08:18.372 --> 08:19.664
...I'm not negotiating.

08:19.874 --> 08:22.626
You understand holding them
indefinitely is the same as...

08:22.835 --> 08:24.669
...dropping them in the ocean.
- No, no.

08:24.879 --> 08:27.881
You leave Mystic Falls and then
give me a call in a few years...

08:28.090 --> 08:30.091
...and we'll talk.

08:31.928 --> 08:34.846
I'm going to give you another chance.
Just one more.

08:35.056 --> 08:36.847
Let's make a reasonable deal.

08:38.768 --> 08:40.018
Or what?

08:40.227 --> 08:42.312
You make one move and I will drop...

08:42.522 --> 08:45.732
Ha, ha, that's right. Crazy Stefan.

08:45.942 --> 08:47.400
Hmm.

08:47.610 --> 08:49.819
How's that working out for you?

08:50.029 --> 08:52.030
Any friends left?

08:59.121 --> 09:00.914
BONNIE:
I can't believe I'm gonna see her.

09:01.123 --> 09:04.626
Or meet her, sort of,
since I don't really remember her.

09:04.835 --> 09:06.920
- You don't talk about her.
- What's to say?

09:07.129 --> 09:11.341
She left, never wrote, never called.
Not even when my grams died.

09:12.802 --> 09:14.761
Could we talk about
you and Damon instead?

09:14.971 --> 09:16.346
I'm not talking about it.

09:19.725 --> 09:22.561
He kissed me.
It's not gonna happen again.

09:24.313 --> 09:27.649
I mean, was it good?

09:28.943 --> 09:31.570
- It doesn't matter.
- That means it was.

09:31.779 --> 09:33.321
[PHONE RINGING]

09:33.531 --> 09:34.948
Oh.

09:35.157 --> 09:38.910
It's Stefan. I told him I'd call him
as soon as I got the address.

09:39.120 --> 09:40.662
Ignore.

09:41.289 --> 09:43.957
You're about to see your mom
for the first time in years.

09:44.166 --> 09:45.959
I'm not letting anyone
ruin that moment.

09:46.168 --> 09:49.087
Yeah, but he's gonna keep at it
until I pick up.

09:49.839 --> 09:51.464
Fine.

09:52.967 --> 09:54.676
- What?
- Where are you?

09:56.387 --> 09:58.763
Bonnie and I are going to
the lake house...

09:58.973 --> 10:01.266
...while we wait for Forbes
to give us addresses.

10:01.475 --> 10:03.476
STEFAN: You're kidding me.
- No, Stefan, I'm not.

10:03.686 --> 10:05.895
We need a night off
from your insanity.

10:06.105 --> 10:08.815
Klaus knows I'm stalling.
We need to move faster.

10:09.025 --> 10:10.317
We're doing everything we can.

10:10.526 --> 10:14.654
So could you maybe not call
every five minutes?

10:15.656 --> 10:18.533
Sure, Elena. Whatever you say.

10:22.121 --> 10:24.497
KLAUS: How's life on the road?
DANIEL [OVER PHONE]: Scenic.

10:24.707 --> 10:27.125
How's life in Mystic Falls
without any hybrids?

10:27.335 --> 10:28.793
Boring. For now.

10:29.003 --> 10:31.296
If you want any of us back,
just say the word.

10:31.505 --> 10:35.050
There's no need. I've been making
friends with the town's civil servants.

10:35.301 --> 10:38.845
There's a deputy who's awfully chatty,
but useful nonetheless.

10:39.055 --> 10:41.348
You clear on what you need to do?

10:41.557 --> 10:43.016
I've got it covered.

11:03.204 --> 11:05.205
- Can I help you?
- Abby Bennett Wilson?

11:05.414 --> 11:06.748
That's me.

11:14.256 --> 11:15.465
ELENA:
Cute house.

11:15.675 --> 11:18.593
BONNIE:
Yeah, for the middle of nowhere.

11:20.971 --> 11:22.013
You ready?

11:24.475 --> 11:25.684
Come on.

11:56.215 --> 11:58.133
JAMIE:
Hey there.

12:00.302 --> 12:04.806
- Hey, we're looking for, um, Abby Wilson.
- She's not home.

12:05.015 --> 12:07.434
- Anything I can do for you?
- It's okay, we can come back.

12:10.396 --> 12:12.397
Sorry, but you look so familiar.

12:12.606 --> 12:14.816
Um, Abby's my mom.

12:16.152 --> 12:17.485
Oh.

12:23.075 --> 12:27.537
I'm Jamie.
Um, you guys wanna come inside?

12:28.122 --> 12:29.205
Right this way.

12:36.338 --> 12:37.922
You sure
you don't want anything?

12:38.132 --> 12:41.843
We got, uh, fresh OJ, coconut water,
some mango-guava something.

12:42.052 --> 12:44.763
- Water's fine.
- Cool.

12:49.059 --> 12:52.228
So, ahem, are we, like, related?

12:52.438 --> 12:56.065
- Oh, no. Uh, Abby's not my mom.
BONNIE: Oh.

12:56.275 --> 12:59.861
- Good.
- She, uh, dated my old man back in the day.

13:00.070 --> 13:02.864
He's kind of a deadbeat.
When they broke up she took me in.

13:03.073 --> 13:07.577
Put me through school. Didn't freak out
when I totaled her car. Twice, heh.

13:07.787 --> 13:11.456
Heh, she sounds great.

13:11.665 --> 13:13.958
- Yeah.
ABBY: Jamie?

13:14.585 --> 13:16.419
Whose car's out front?

13:18.214 --> 13:19.464
That's mine.

13:26.013 --> 13:27.972
I'm Bonnie.

13:29.642 --> 13:30.725
Your daughter.

13:31.936 --> 13:33.269
[SIGHS]

13:36.816 --> 13:39.150
Hello, Bonnie.

13:44.114 --> 13:46.950
- How do you know this is gonna work?
BILL: Ah, it's a process.

13:47.159 --> 13:49.744
It took decades to train myself
to resist compulsion.

13:49.954 --> 13:53.289
Brain's like a muscle.
The more you use it, the more it can do.

13:53.499 --> 13:58.211
The sire bond, at its core,
is about one thing.

13:58.420 --> 14:01.422
Gratitude.
You believe you owe Klaus your life.

14:01.632 --> 14:05.385
- Ask yourself why.
- I was cursed.

14:05.636 --> 14:08.596
Every full moon,
I had to change into a wolf.

14:08.806 --> 14:10.890
It was torture. Klaus took that away.

14:11.141 --> 14:13.810
He freed you from your pain,
you feel indebted to him.

14:14.019 --> 14:18.147
To break the sire bond,
you gotta make yourself turn.

14:20.317 --> 14:23.820
Own your pain, then you'll owe
Klaus nothing and you'll be free.

14:24.655 --> 14:27.073
But how can he turn?
It's not a full moon.

14:27.283 --> 14:29.659
He doesn't need one.
You're a hybrid now, right?

14:29.869 --> 14:32.287
I mean, you can turn at will or not,
am I right?

14:32.496 --> 14:35.290
Yeah, but I don't know
how to just start.

14:35.499 --> 14:37.750
- You're making excuses.
TYLER: You don't understand.

14:37.960 --> 14:40.044
When I turn,
I break every bone in my body.

14:40.254 --> 14:42.922
You asked for my help,
this is the only way.

14:43.173 --> 14:45.466
How badly do you want
your freedom?

14:51.390 --> 14:54.058
- Okay.
BILL: Okay.

15:12.119 --> 15:13.703
[GASPS]

15:14.121 --> 15:15.538
[GRUNTS]

15:15.748 --> 15:17.457
[PANTS]

15:18.876 --> 15:20.793
[SCREAMS]

15:24.882 --> 15:28.718
ELENA: How are you holding up?
- I'll be fine.

15:28.928 --> 15:31.554
I'm not here to get my mom back.
I'm here to get help.

15:31.764 --> 15:34.641
ABBY:
So I hope you guys are hungry...

15:34.850 --> 15:39.062
...because, uh, food has always been
my go-to icebreaker.

15:39.271 --> 15:41.356
- You have a really beautiful home.
ABBY: Ha, ha.

15:41.565 --> 15:44.359
You're so sweet. Just like your mom.

15:47.488 --> 15:50.615
- You knew my mom?
- Miranda was my best friend.

15:51.867 --> 15:54.535
You had a daughter and a best friend
and you still left?

15:54.745 --> 15:56.829
My best friend is why I left.

15:58.749 --> 16:02.043
Fifteen years ago,
a vampire came to town...

16:02.252 --> 16:05.880
...looking for you, Elena.
Looking for the doppelganger.

16:06.674 --> 16:09.384
No one could manage to kill him...

16:09.593 --> 16:13.846
...so I lured him out of town
and cast a spell to desiccate him...

16:14.056 --> 16:15.807
...in a crypt in Charlotte.

16:16.016 --> 16:19.435
Mikael. He was an Original vampire.

16:19.645 --> 16:22.563
It took every ounce of power I had.

16:23.399 --> 16:25.358
Almost killed me.

16:26.485 --> 16:30.154
I recovered, but my magic didn't.

16:30.364 --> 16:34.158
- My powers never came back.
- Neither did you.

16:36.036 --> 16:37.704
- It wasn't that simple.
BONNIE: It wasn't?

16:37.913 --> 16:40.915
You cast a spell, put Mikael down
and what?

16:41.125 --> 16:43.209
- Had to teach Jamie how to drive?
- Bonnie.

16:43.419 --> 16:46.671
This was a mistake.
She has no magic, she can't help us.

16:46.880 --> 16:48.965
Bonnie, wait, please!

16:50.092 --> 16:52.301
Don't go. Talk to me.

16:52.511 --> 16:54.220
Please?

16:54.722 --> 16:56.180
ELENA:
I'll wait outside.

17:12.990 --> 17:16.075
- Aah!
- Hi, Elena. Nice lake house.

17:20.247 --> 17:21.372
WOMAN [OVER PA]:
Dr. Raymond to the ER.

17:21.582 --> 17:25.835
You know, we never got a chance
to officially meet, Dr. Fell.

17:26.045 --> 17:28.296
You're Alaric's friend, right?

17:28.505 --> 17:31.340
Damon Salvatore.
I saw you at the Council meeting.

17:31.550 --> 17:33.092
What are you doing here?

17:34.136 --> 17:38.264
Strolling the halls. I like to wave
at the newborns through the window.

17:39.266 --> 17:42.351
Sorry about your boyfriend.
Animal attack.

17:43.353 --> 17:45.688
- Brutal.
- Ex-boyfriend.

17:45.898 --> 17:48.274
And thanks,
I'm still kind of processing.

17:48.484 --> 17:52.487
Yeah, I'm sure. I thought I'd come by
and tell you it wasn't an animal attack.

17:52.696 --> 17:55.073
And then I realized...

17:55.908 --> 17:58.076
...you signed the death certificate.

18:08.962 --> 18:10.671
Would you rather I say
he was staked?

18:10.881 --> 18:13.883
Wasn't he the guy that
coined the phrase "animal attack"?

18:14.093 --> 18:16.177
- Why do you care?
- Because Ric likes you.

18:16.386 --> 18:18.763
If you're a psychopath,
that would suck for him.

18:18.972 --> 18:20.473
You think I killed my boyfriend?

18:20.682 --> 18:23.184
I think psychopaths
are incredibly high-maintenance.

18:23.894 --> 18:27.522
If you care about your friend, go figure
out how Alaric came into the ICU...

18:27.731 --> 18:31.526
...on his death bed and walked out
an hour later without a scratch.

18:35.405 --> 18:36.572
Fair enough.

18:40.911 --> 18:42.286
[DAMON GRUNTS]

18:58.428 --> 18:59.929
[GROANS]

19:09.523 --> 19:10.940
[TYLER SCREAMING AND GRUNTING]

19:23.412 --> 19:25.705
I can't. I can't.

19:25.914 --> 19:29.125
- Try harder.
- Can't he just rest for one second?

19:29.334 --> 19:31.794
We're doing this my way.
If you can't handle it, go.

19:32.004 --> 19:33.921
- He's right, Caroline. Just go.
CAROLINE: No.

19:34.131 --> 19:35.923
- Tyler...
- Go, Caroline!

19:37.551 --> 19:39.510
[PANTING]

19:44.808 --> 19:45.892
[TYLER GRUNTING]

19:58.071 --> 19:59.947
What are you doing?

20:00.157 --> 20:02.950
- What the hell, man?
- Does that bother you?

20:03.160 --> 20:05.203
- Knock it off!
- Good. Get angry.

20:05.412 --> 20:07.705
- It's in you. You know it is.
- Unh.

20:07.915 --> 20:09.749
I said knock it off!

20:13.879 --> 20:16.380
Your bond to Klaus
is putting my daughter in danger.

20:16.590 --> 20:20.927
Either you turn
or I kill you right here, right now.

20:29.019 --> 20:32.021
[SCREAMING AND GRUNTING]

20:43.909 --> 20:46.535
You've grown into such a beautiful
young woman, Bonnie.

20:46.745 --> 20:50.414
Please just stop with the muffins
and the compliments.

20:50.624 --> 20:53.292
I just wanna know the truth.

20:53.877 --> 20:55.378
Why didn't you come home?

20:57.923 --> 20:59.799
[SIGHS]

21:00.801 --> 21:03.427
I had no magic. I was in a new city...

21:03.637 --> 21:07.431
...and I realized I had a chance
to be somebody else.

21:07.975 --> 21:11.185
To be Abby Wilson the woman...

21:11.395 --> 21:12.937
...not Abby Bennett the witch.

21:15.899 --> 21:18.651
I'm not proud of what I did, Bonnie.

21:19.820 --> 21:21.612
I ran.

21:22.155 --> 21:23.572
I know I ran.

21:23.782 --> 21:27.159
But you had your dad and your grams,
and, okay, let's face it...

21:27.411 --> 21:31.622
...your grams is way better at this stuff
than I am.

21:32.165 --> 21:33.624
You don't know?

21:36.420 --> 21:37.503
What?

21:46.430 --> 21:51.017
- How?
- We were doing a rough spell...

21:51.768 --> 21:54.520
...and we both exhausted ourselves.

21:56.523 --> 21:58.774
Her more than me.

22:06.283 --> 22:07.867
ABBY:
Well, she raised you right.

22:09.202 --> 22:11.579
I'm sure she would've been
very proud of you.

22:18.795 --> 22:22.131
Well, now you know my whole story.

22:22.341 --> 22:23.799
Yup, heh.

22:24.009 --> 22:26.761
How about you tell me yours?

22:26.970 --> 22:28.721
What brings you to me?

22:29.556 --> 22:31.974
It was a dream, actually.

22:32.184 --> 22:34.310
I thought you
were supposed to help us.

22:35.354 --> 22:37.438
But if you don't have any magic,
it's...

22:37.647 --> 22:43.486
Well, now, spells, no,
but I'm not completely useless.

22:43.695 --> 22:45.863
And the earth still provides
herbs and such.

22:46.073 --> 22:49.658
- There might be something I can do.
- I don't think so.

22:49.868 --> 22:52.536
Bonnie, please.

22:53.413 --> 22:54.872
Let me help you.

22:57.584 --> 22:59.001
You think I wouldn't find out?

22:59.211 --> 23:00.544
Honestly, I didn't care.

23:00.754 --> 23:02.880
This is why
I didn't want you in the loop.

23:03.090 --> 23:05.341
Because now you can't
do whatever you want.

23:05.675 --> 23:06.842
STEFAN:
Unh. Damn it.

23:07.052 --> 23:08.719
JAMIE:
Hey!

23:08.929 --> 23:10.763
- Everything all right out here?
ELENA: Hey.

23:11.431 --> 23:13.641
Jamie, go back inside, okay?

23:13.850 --> 23:16.727
Please. Trust me,
it's better off for you there.

23:17.771 --> 23:19.688
I don't think so.

23:19.898 --> 23:22.733
I'd listen to her.
Get back upstairs, man.

23:22.943 --> 23:24.276
I said, I don't think so.

23:25.570 --> 23:28.572
Get back upstairs
before I tear your damn throat out...

23:28.782 --> 23:30.032
...do you understand me?

23:32.202 --> 23:34.453
I don't think you realize
how bad you've gotten.

23:34.663 --> 23:37.373
- It's the way it has to be, Elena.
ELENA: Oh, yeah, right.

23:37.582 --> 23:38.874
Out-villain the villain.

23:39.084 --> 23:40.209
I get it.

23:40.419 --> 23:43.045
- You're not supposed to be here.
ELENA: What are you doing?

23:43.255 --> 23:45.714
It's what I was told.
He's not supposed to be here.

23:45.924 --> 23:48.426
- Elena, he's compelled.
- Aah!

23:48.635 --> 23:50.594
What was that?

23:54.808 --> 23:56.976
[GRUNTING]

24:05.861 --> 24:08.362
ALARIC: What are you doing here?
DAMON: Ah, looking for a bunny.

24:10.365 --> 24:11.907
You're good. For now.

24:12.117 --> 24:14.326
You still obsessed with Meredith?

24:14.536 --> 24:15.911
[GRUNTS]

24:16.121 --> 24:18.122
Don't you have
an Original vampire to worry about?

24:18.331 --> 24:20.499
Uh-uh-uh. Do 10 more of those.

24:21.001 --> 24:23.627
You're gonna wanna buff up
if you start dating this one.

24:23.879 --> 24:26.130
- Self-defense and all.
- What is your problem?

24:26.339 --> 24:28.466
Your doctor vervained me.

24:28.675 --> 24:30.843
And then she blood-jacked me.

24:31.052 --> 24:33.804
What? I mean,
when did you even see her?

24:34.014 --> 24:36.557
When I went to accuse her
of killing her ex-boyfriend.

24:36.766 --> 24:38.893
Which, by the way,
very sensitive subject.

24:39.144 --> 24:40.769
Damon, what the hell
are you doing, huh?

24:40.979 --> 24:43.355
- Why are you mad?
- I told you I'd handle this.

24:43.565 --> 24:47.193
I proved your theory.
Diagnosed psycho case.

24:47.402 --> 24:49.069
You're welcome.

24:52.115 --> 24:53.157
[ELENA GRUNTS]

24:53.366 --> 24:55.701
ELENA: Why are doing this?
- Stop moving.

24:55.911 --> 24:58.078
[STEFAN GROANS]

24:58.288 --> 25:01.081
Jamie, let me go.
Jamie, he needs help.

25:01.291 --> 25:02.833
ABBY: Jamie!
- Bonnie.

25:04.711 --> 25:06.337
Bonnie!

25:15.305 --> 25:16.889
[GRUNTS]

25:17.098 --> 25:18.140
[SCREAMING AND GRUNTING]

25:37.577 --> 25:40.371
- Oh, my God.
TYLER: These chains aren't strong enough.

25:40.580 --> 25:41.956
You need to leave.

25:42.165 --> 25:44.083
Run!

25:50.966 --> 25:52.841
[ROARS]

26:08.775 --> 26:11.068
DANIEL: So?
- She didn't tell me where the coffins are.

26:11.278 --> 26:12.820
The vampire showed up.

26:13.029 --> 26:14.613
Did Jamie take care of it?

26:14.823 --> 26:16.657
He did.

26:16.866 --> 26:20.995
But she's not gonna talk now.
There's no way. I tried.

26:21.204 --> 26:22.788
Well, you should try again.

26:30.547 --> 26:32.798
- What'd you do to me?
- You'll be fine.

26:33.008 --> 26:35.968
Don't try any spells.
Those herbs I used muted your magic.

26:37.220 --> 26:40.180
- Where's Elena?
- She'll be fine too. Bonnie, listen to me.

26:40.390 --> 26:44.268
I need your help. I need you
to tell me where those coffins are.

26:44.477 --> 26:45.519
Why?

26:45.729 --> 26:50.232
Because if you don't, that man
compelled Jamie to kill himself.

26:55.530 --> 26:57.031
I can't.

26:58.241 --> 27:00.326
This goes beyond you and me.

27:05.874 --> 27:08.709
ABBY: All you need to do is tell me
where they are...

27:08.918 --> 27:11.337
...then we'll have held up
our end of the bargain.

27:11.546 --> 27:13.589
Bonnie, please.

27:22.140 --> 27:23.390
[ELENA GRUNTING]

27:23.600 --> 27:25.059
ELENA:
I've almost got it.

27:25.685 --> 27:29.104
[GRUNTING]

27:34.778 --> 27:36.779
Abby hasn't called yet.

27:36.988 --> 27:38.572
Jamie, please, just let us go.

27:38.782 --> 27:41.533
Don't. Please, don't do anything.

27:42.285 --> 27:44.912
I don't know why I shot him,
why I'm holding this gun...

27:45.121 --> 27:47.873
...but if you do anything,
I'm gonna shoot him again.

27:48.083 --> 27:50.084
ELENA:
Okay, I won't.

27:50.293 --> 27:53.420
- Who gave you that gun?
- A man came by here earlier today.

27:53.630 --> 27:56.840
He said it was wooden buckshot.
Told me if anyone got in our way...

27:57.050 --> 27:58.509
...I'm supposed to shoot him.

27:58.802 --> 28:00.636
What else did he say?

28:01.221 --> 28:04.431
If Abby didn't find the locations
of some coffins...

28:04.641 --> 28:06.934
...I'm supposed to shoot myself.

28:09.229 --> 28:10.813
What about me?

28:11.022 --> 28:12.398
What did he say about me?

28:14.526 --> 28:16.235
I'm not supposed to hurt you.

28:17.737 --> 28:19.196
[SIGHS]

28:20.031 --> 28:23.450
Well, are you sure?
Because these ropes are so tight...

28:23.660 --> 28:25.661
...that it is hurting me.

28:31.459 --> 28:32.876
[JAMIE GRUNTS]

28:37.048 --> 28:38.090
What can I do to help?

28:38.967 --> 28:41.218
Every time I move,
the wood shifts inside of me.

28:41.428 --> 28:43.971
I can feel it scraping against my heart.

28:44.180 --> 28:46.765
- You need to get the pieces out.
- Ugh.

28:53.940 --> 28:54.982
[STEFAN YELLS]

29:02.532 --> 29:05.159
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

29:08.663 --> 29:10.831
What took you so long?

29:16.963 --> 29:19.965
Hiding behind your witchy friends.

29:20.175 --> 29:22.885
And in squalor, no less.

29:23.094 --> 29:24.428
[SCREAMING]

29:29.851 --> 29:32.603
Insulting a bunch of dead witches?
Not smart.

29:32.812 --> 29:35.189
I made the same mistake
first time I came in here.

29:35.398 --> 29:37.775
Well, you know,
the funny thing about witches...

29:37.984 --> 29:41.487
...is that living or dead,
they care about their own.

29:44.491 --> 29:49.077
A hundred dead witches
have a thousand living descendants.

29:49.287 --> 29:51.663
[SCREAMING]

29:51.873 --> 29:56.168
And I have no problem
killing every last one of them...

29:56.377 --> 29:58.378
...if I don't get my coffins back.

29:58.588 --> 30:03.300
As we speak, my hybrid friend
is prepared to end the Bennett line.

30:06.554 --> 30:08.680
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

30:16.022 --> 30:17.523
Now.

30:18.733 --> 30:23.195
Please, show me the coffins.

30:31.579 --> 30:33.580
Here we are.

30:38.419 --> 30:39.545
Where's the fourth?

30:44.342 --> 30:45.384
Show me!

30:47.887 --> 30:52.724
Well, uh, here's the thing. They can't.

30:53.560 --> 30:55.352
It's not here.

30:56.229 --> 30:59.857
- What did you do?
- Well, Bonnie gave me the heads up.

31:00.066 --> 31:05.487
I mean, I didn't have enough time to get
all four, but I did have time to get one.

31:09.367 --> 31:12.160
I will tear you limb from limb.

31:12.370 --> 31:17.165
And only then, when you're
a writhing mass of blood and flesh...

31:17.375 --> 31:20.294
...will I rip your heart from your chest.

31:20.503 --> 31:22.379
Sorry.

31:22.589 --> 31:24.840
Same rules apply.

31:25.049 --> 31:26.091
Leverage and all.

31:26.676 --> 31:28.719
I know you want your family back.

31:28.928 --> 31:33.599
But something tells me
you want what's in that coffin a lot more.

31:43.443 --> 31:45.944
- Tell me what you're up to.
- You talked to Damon.

31:46.154 --> 31:47.779
- Yeah.
- Wasn't supposed to wake up.

31:47.989 --> 31:50.324
I used enough vervain
to sedate him for hours.

31:50.533 --> 31:54.703
He drinks it to build up an immunity
so people don't get the jump on him.

31:54.913 --> 31:57.080
- I'm not crazy, Ric.
- Then what are you?

31:57.290 --> 31:58.332
Watch your back.

31:58.958 --> 32:00.709
You really wanna know?

32:00.960 --> 32:02.336
Stick around.

32:05.965 --> 32:07.633
Is that Bill Forbes?

32:07.842 --> 32:10.052
[GRUNTING]

32:15.683 --> 32:19.603
- I'm just trying to help.
- Just get it out, Elena, please.

32:19.812 --> 32:21.688
Just get it out.

32:22.315 --> 32:25.067
Keep squirming,
maybe I'll feel sorry for you.

32:25.276 --> 32:26.818
[GASPS]

32:38.206 --> 32:39.539
You've changed.

32:40.750 --> 32:43.168
Something's different about you.

32:43.378 --> 32:46.505
You're stronger. Tougher.

32:51.386 --> 32:54.346
You're not the only one
who changed, Stefan.

32:56.015 --> 32:57.391
We all had to.

32:57.850 --> 32:59.017
[CHUCKLES]

32:59.227 --> 33:01.019
It's good, though.

33:06.025 --> 33:08.235
There's something I have to tell you.

33:09.362 --> 33:12.614
And it's not because
I feel guilty that it happened...

33:14.033 --> 33:15.701
...it's just I feel guilty you don't know.

33:15.910 --> 33:17.327
[GRUNTS]

33:20.540 --> 33:22.207
[SIGHS]

33:22.417 --> 33:24.626
I kissed Damon.

33:46.399 --> 33:48.316
There. All done.

34:17.472 --> 34:18.513
ALARIC:
What happened?

34:18.723 --> 34:21.183
MEREDITH: He was found in the woods.
An actual animal attack.

34:21.391 --> 34:23.268
Bite marks over half his body.

34:23.478 --> 34:26.103
- Lost about three liters of blood.
- Is he gonna make it?

34:26.313 --> 34:28.815
Nope. At least, not on his own.

34:31.152 --> 34:33.195
- What is that?
- What you think it is.

34:33.404 --> 34:34.446
Vampire blood.

34:39.659 --> 34:41.620
You wanted to know my secret?
I cheat.

34:41.829 --> 34:43.205
I hate when people die.

34:43.414 --> 34:47.542
So when I have the ability
to do something about it, I do.

34:54.967 --> 34:56.885
Stefan.

34:59.806 --> 35:01.556
Say something.

35:02.975 --> 35:04.017
Please?

35:04.227 --> 35:06.686
I shouldn't have kidnapped you.

35:10.149 --> 35:13.068
The car, the bridge. It was too far.

35:15.363 --> 35:16.780
Thank you.

35:16.989 --> 35:20.742
But you shouldn't have lied to me.
You can't go off and do things like that.

35:20.952 --> 35:23.662
- Not while Klaus is still alive.
- I know.

35:24.539 --> 35:29.835
I just... I wanted to give Bonnie
a moment with her mother...

35:30.294 --> 35:32.838
...without everything else getting
in the way.

35:34.841 --> 35:36.758
Without me getting in the way.

35:48.396 --> 35:50.981
I didn't plan on kissing him.

35:52.108 --> 35:54.025
You're better than him, Elena.

35:58.447 --> 36:00.157
You're better than both of us.

36:16.591 --> 36:18.383
BONNIE:
Elena's on her way.

36:18.593 --> 36:20.218
Jamie's safe.

36:20.428 --> 36:22.262
He's a little bruised, but he's safe.

36:23.222 --> 36:24.723
Think the hybrid will come back?

36:24.932 --> 36:27.976
You kept your end of the bargain.
Klaus usually keeps his.

36:31.022 --> 36:33.899
You were willing to do
all this for him...

36:34.734 --> 36:37.611
...and he's not even your family.
- He is my family, Bonnie.

36:38.487 --> 36:41.031
I know that might be hard
for you to hear, but he is.

36:42.950 --> 36:45.493
But that doesn't mean
I don't care about you.

36:46.245 --> 36:48.705
- I wanna help you.
- You can't.

36:48.915 --> 36:52.042
You have no magic,
and I don't trust you.

36:56.380 --> 36:58.757
When I put Mikael down...

36:59.634 --> 37:01.426
...my magic didn't just leave me.

37:02.136 --> 37:03.511
It drifted away.

37:03.721 --> 37:07.015
The longer I stayed away from you,
the weaker it got.

37:08.643 --> 37:11.937
I think nature was punishing me
for abandoning you.

37:17.735 --> 37:20.028
Maybe you can help me
get my magic back.

37:20.238 --> 37:22.572
I thought you said
you didn't want it anymore.

37:23.115 --> 37:24.491
I don't.

37:25.076 --> 37:29.287
But if it's what you wanted,
I would do that for you.

37:39.465 --> 37:40.840
- You're better.
BILL: Yeah.

37:41.050 --> 37:44.010
I shouldn't be,
but I didn't have any say in the matter.

37:46.681 --> 37:48.181
I didn't mean to hurt you.

37:48.391 --> 37:50.350
I lost control.

37:50.559 --> 37:51.935
Again.

37:52.144 --> 37:54.688
I knew the risks
when I decided to help you.

37:54.897 --> 37:56.398
[SIGHS]

37:56.607 --> 37:59.192
So was it worth it? How do you feel?

37:59.402 --> 38:01.653
Different. A little more myself.

38:02.530 --> 38:03.905
Then we'll continue tomorrow.

38:04.115 --> 38:06.491
What are you talking about? I turned.

38:07.034 --> 38:11.955
Once. To break the sire bond,
turning needs to be painless.

38:12.164 --> 38:17.168
And from what I saw today,
we're still a long way off.

38:18.379 --> 38:20.255
I can't put myself through that again.

38:20.464 --> 38:23.967
You will. Because until you're capable
of acting on your own free will...

38:24.176 --> 38:27.137
...I'm not gonna let you anywhere near
my daughter.

38:34.061 --> 38:36.146
You told me your secret...

38:37.189 --> 38:39.107
...and this is mine.

38:39.317 --> 38:40.900
You're a vampire hunter.

38:41.110 --> 38:43.445
Semi-retired.

38:46.782 --> 38:49.034
You're trying to get out of
taking me to dinner.

38:49.243 --> 38:50.910
I just wanna be honest.

38:51.287 --> 38:52.912
No secrets.

38:53.122 --> 38:54.456
Okay.

38:54.665 --> 38:57.208
Then tell me how you survived
getting hit by a truck.

38:57.418 --> 39:00.128
Your injuries were fatal.
Was it vampire blood?

39:00.338 --> 39:03.798
That and, uh, this ring.

39:04.008 --> 39:07.135
It protects me from death
at the hands of supernatural beings.

39:07.345 --> 39:11.514
Vampire hunter
who can't be killed by vampires.

39:11.724 --> 39:13.975
Convenient, heh.

39:16.937 --> 39:19.981
Are you worried
I'm a supernatural being?

39:20.191 --> 39:24.361
Hmm, one can never be too careful.

39:26.447 --> 39:27.489
[DOOR OPENS]

39:31.077 --> 39:32.952
Oh, um, hey. Um...

39:33.162 --> 39:34.245
Sorry.

39:34.455 --> 39:37.540
- Uh, I'm gonna go.
- Okay, yeah. Sure, sure, sure.

39:41.170 --> 39:43.171
Elena, I am s... I'm sorry.

39:43.381 --> 39:44.756
Please, it's okay.

39:44.965 --> 39:47.092
It's not okay.
I mean, it's not even my place.

39:47.301 --> 39:51.221
It's your place, it's Jenna's place,
it's your family's place.

39:51.430 --> 39:55.141
The minute you slept on that couch
it became your place too.

39:56.185 --> 39:58.812
We needed you and...

39:59.688 --> 40:01.731
[SIGHS]

40:01.941 --> 40:03.733
And you stayed.

40:03.943 --> 40:05.568
So thank you for that.

40:06.570 --> 40:08.947
Hey, look, I know it's hard.

40:11.575 --> 40:12.992
But Jenna's gone.

40:14.578 --> 40:17.080
And you're allowed to move on.

40:29.218 --> 40:31.219
STEFAN:
Oh, you're still alive?

40:31.429 --> 40:33.721
I assume that means Klaus
didn't get his coffins.

40:33.931 --> 40:35.515
DAMON:
Don't look so happy.

40:35.724 --> 40:38.268
I was only able to get one
of them out in time.

40:38.477 --> 40:39.978
The locked one.

40:40.187 --> 40:42.272
- Probably a good choice.
- Yeah.

40:42.481 --> 40:45.567
If you're banking on Bonnie's momma
to open it, you're screwed.

40:45.776 --> 40:49.946
- She doesn't have any powers.
- Yeah. Doesn't surprise me.

40:50.156 --> 40:52.115
It's been that kind of night.

40:52.324 --> 40:54.117
Is Elena okay?

40:58.164 --> 40:59.747
[DAMON GRUNTS]

41:01.083 --> 41:04.127
I take it you two had a heart-to-heart.

41:07.423 --> 41:10.383
And I take it
you don't wanna talk about it.

41:10.593 --> 41:12.135
Noted.

41:12.553 --> 41:14.762
So why don't we talk about this?

41:17.266 --> 41:19.309
What did you do?

41:24.899 --> 41:27.775
You've got your family back finally.

41:29.487 --> 41:31.070
You gonna open them?

41:31.739 --> 41:33.323
Not quite yet.

41:34.074 --> 41:37.118
I still have some unfinished business
to take care of.

41:37.328 --> 41:39.579
What business?

41:39.914 --> 41:42.248
[GRUNTS]

41:44.919 --> 41:46.377
So Niklaus.

41:46.921 --> 41:48.129
Elijah.

41:50.841 --> 41:52.926
What did I miss?

